Response:
  The Executive Office of the President (EOP) is a group of agencies responsible for supporting the President of the United States. 
  The EOP is headed by the White House Chief of Staff and includes various offices, such as the Office of the First Lady, the Office of the Press Secretary, and the Office of Management and Budget. 
  The EOP is composed of about 1,800 staff members who work closely with the President to develop and implement policies, respond to crises, and communicate with the public.
